      "id": "nmusd-mrca-negotiations-may-2026",
      "category": "OFFICIAL",
      "date": "May 19, 2026",
      "title": "NMUSD Board Holds Closed Session on Banning Ranch Land Sale Negotiations with MRCA",
      "summary": "The Newport-Mesa Unified School District (NMUSD) Board of Education held a closed session on May 19, 2026, to confer with real property negotiators regarding the district-owned 11.36-acre Banning Ranch land, adjacent to the Randall Preserve. This follows NMUSD's receipt of a letter from the Mountains Recreation and Conservation Authority (MRCA) in March 2026 expressing interest in the surplus land for open space purposes, leading to good faith negotiations for mutually satisfactory lease or purchase terms.",
      "source": "Stu News Newport",
      "sentiment": "NEUTRAL"
    },
    {
      "id": "coastal-corridor-alliance-new-mission-may-2026",
      "category": "LOCAL",
      "date": "May 17, 2026",
      "title": "Coastal Corridor Alliance Broadens Mission to Protect Randall Preserve and Coastal Ecosystems",
      "summary": "The Coastal Corridor Alliance, formerly Banning Ranch Conservancy, announced an expansion of its mission on May 17, 2026, to encompass the protection and rejuvenation of vital ecosystems along the Santa Ana River Coastal Corridor, including the Randall Preserve. The organization encourages community engagement through volunteerism, learning, and future planning, and has also launched a new merchandise store to support its conservation efforts.",
      "source": "Coastal Corridor Alliance",
      "sentiment": "POSITIVE"
    },
    {
      "id": "reddit-randall-preserve-discussion-may-2026-v2",
      "category": "SOCIAL",
      "date": "May 13, 2026",
      "title": "Reddit Users Discuss Randall Preserve's Development History and Environmental Concerns",
      "summary": "A Reddit thread on r/orangecounty recently featured a user inquiring about the history of the Randall Preserve, expressing surprise that the area was preserved rather than developed for retail/residential use. The user also raised questions about whether it was a toxic waste site and the influence of developers, indicating ongoing community interest and some skepticism about the preserve's past.",
      "source": "Reddit (r/orangecounty)",
      "sentiment": "MIXED"
    },
    {
      "id": "reddit-randall-preserve-story-may-2026",
      "category": "SOCIAL",
      "date": "May 10, 2026",
      "title": "Reddit Community Discusses History and Future of Randall Preserve",
      "summary": "A recent Reddit thread on r/orangecounty explored the history of Banning Ranch becoming the Randall Preserve, including the significant $50 million donation from Frank and Joann Randall for its acquisition. The discussion touched on the area's past as an oil well site and ongoing efforts for tribal recognition, highlighting community engagement in its preservation.",
      "source": "Reddit (r/orangecounty)",
      "sentiment": "MIXED"
    },
    {
      "id": "randall-preserve-nmusd-property-may-2026",
      "category": "LOCAL",
      "date": "May 04, 2026",
      "title": "Randall Preserve Advocates Urge NMUSD to Sell Adjacent Land for Preservation",
      "summary": "The Mountains Recreation and Conservation Authority (MRCA) and Randall Preserve advocates are urging the Newport Mesa Unified School District (NMUSD) to negotiate the sale of an 11.36-acre parcel adjacent to the preserve. The property, which currently juts into the preserve, contains sensitive habitats and species, and conservationists aim to prevent its development and incorporate it into the preserve's open space. Community members are encouraged to contact NMUSD to support the sale.",
      "source": "Coastal Open Space Advocates",
      "sentiment": "MIXED"
    },
